parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can lead to engine failure, stalling, and potentially cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle consumes excessive amounts of oil between oil changes
often requiring frequent oil top-ups
and may exhibit warning lights on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or catch fire, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The engine may suddenly fail or catch fire while driving
often accompanied by warning lights on the dashboard
smoke
or unusual noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Oil leaks can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs or even engine failure.
symptoms: Oil leaks may be visible
or the vehicle may exhibit low oil levels
warning lights on the dashboard
or unusual noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear suspension can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, and can also result in premature tire wear, uneven tire wear, and difficulty maintaining proper wheel alignment.
symptoms: Loud noises from the rear of the vehicle
uneven tire wear
difficulty maintaining proper wheel alignment
loose or broken rear suspension arms
grinding noises from the back of the car
and inability to drive in a straight line.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inability to obtain recall repairs can lead to continued safety risks and potential accidents due to unresolved safety issues.
symptoms: Unavailability of parts
excessive wait times for repairs
and lack of communication from dealerships and manufacturers.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the sway bar can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, and can also result in uneven tire wear and difficulty maintaining proper wheel alignment.
symptoms: Loud noises from the rear of the vehicle
uneven tire wear
difficulty maintaining proper wheel alignment
and broken sway bar bolts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can lead to premature engine wear, overheating, and potentially cause engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle consumes excessive amounts of oil
requiring frequent oil changes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the steering column can cause loss of steering control, leading to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The steering wheel makes a loud clunking noise
becomes loose or free-floating
and may cause the air vent to fall on the driver's foot.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the power steering system can cause loss of steering control, leading to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The power steering light comes on
the steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
and the vehicle may make a clicking or clunking noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the intermediate steering shaft can cause loss of steering control, leading to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The steering wheel makes a clunking or knocking noise
and the vehicle may vibrate or shake while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the rack and pinion can cause loss of steering control, leading to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The vehicle makes a clicking or knocking noise while turning
and the steering wheel may vibrate or shake.
